The '''Institute for Computational and Experimental Research in Mathematics (ICERM)''', founded in 2011, is a research institute in [[mathematics]] at [[Brown University]], funded beginning in 2010 by a grant from the [[National Science Foundation]]. It is located in downtown [[Providence, Rhode Island]].<ref>{{citation|title= Institute for Computational and Experimental Research in Mathematics|first=Jill|last=Pipher|date=September 2013|pages=45–47|url=http://www.ems-ph.org/journals/newsletter/pdf/2013-09-89.pdf|journal=[[Newsletter of the European Mathematical Society]]|volume=89}}.</ref>
==Directors of ICERM== * [[Jill Pipher]] (2011–2016) * [[Brendan Hassett]] (2016–present)
